## Launch overview — detail

## What Sonnet CAN safely do

- **Update counts** in hero, bento, rail stats, timeline, theme rows — text only; do not restructure grids.
- **Refresh theme lists** via `uv run scripts/tbpro_launch_overview.py` (post-approval) or copy fresh output into one `<!-- SECTION: … -->` block at a time.
- **Fix copy** in hero, insights, glossary, footer — see `tbpro-copy-tone.mdc`.
- **Add theme rows** inside `#themes .themes` using template below; bar width = `style="width:N%"` on `.theme-row__bar` only.

**Python constants:** `tbpro_launch_overview.py` — `LAUNCH_DATE`, `WAVES`, `EXCLUDE_IDS`, `MANUAL_THEMES`, `LAUNCH_WATCH_ONLY`. `tbpro_daily.py` — `LAUNCH_DATE`, `INVITEE_COUNT`, `EXCLUDE_IDS`, `WATCH_PROBLEMS`, `MANUAL_THEMES`.

## What requires caution

- **Chart.js** — bottom `<script>`: edit `dates`/`daily` arrays only; do not refactor chart config.
- **IntersectionObserver** — scroll-spy / `setActiveNav()`; touch only for a reported bug.
- **CSS tokens** — `:root` only (`/* CSS REGION: tokens */`); no raw hex in component rules.

## Forbidden without Lisa review

- Raw Zendesk `subject` in HTML — use generic paraphrase (`#6125 — Payment processing delay`, not API text).
- `display:flex` on `th`/`td` — see `tbpro-table-patterns.mdc`.
- Re-adding **Still open** panel or blocker-column pattern.
- Editing `launch_overview.html`, `tbpro_launch_overview.py`, or `latest.html` before sample approval.
- PII: emails, names, domains, raw ticket bodies.

## File map — `launch_overview_sample.html`

Jump via `<!-- SECTION: name -->`: `#story` hero+bento · `#waves` timeline · `#volume` charts · `#aht` resolution time · `#planning` staffing · `#themes` theme blocks+misdirect · `#ideas` kanban+table · `#engineering` eng cards · `#glossary` definitions.

CSS regions in `<style>`: tokens → layout → components → tables → themes.

## Update workflow

1. Fetch: `uv run scripts/tbpro_launch_overview.py` (Zendesk creds required).
2. Update Python constants if waves/exclusions changed.
3. Edit one HTML section at a time via section comments.
4. Grep for PII (`@`, phone patterns) before commit; footer must include *"Ticket subjects paraphrased…"*.

## HTML templates (copy-paste)

**Theme row:**

```html
<div class="theme-row-wrap">
  <div class="theme-row">
    <span class="theme-row__name">Theme label</span>
    <span class="theme-row__count">4<span class="theme-row__pct">13%</span></span>
    <div class="theme-row__bar-wrap"><div class="theme-row__bar" style="width:100%"></div></div>
  </div>
  <details class="theme-tickets">
    <summary>4 tickets</summary>
    <ul class="theme-tickets__list">
      <li><a href="https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/1234" target="_blank">#1234</a><span class="theme-tickets__subj"> — Paraphrased description</span></li>
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>
```

**Eng card** (`--open` | `--hold` | `--solved`):

```html
<div class="eng-card eng-card--open">
  <div><div class="eng-card__id eng-card__id--open"><a href="https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/6068" target="_blank">#6068</a></div><div class="eng-card__gh"><a href="https://github.com/thunderbird/repo/issues/123" target="_blank">repo#123</a></div></div>
  <div class="eng-card__subject">Paraphrased issue summary</div>
  <div class="eng-card__date">2026-06-05</div>
</div>
```

Non-English tickets: paraphrase + `*(Language — "translation")*`.
